{"questionId":"33299112","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>|</mo><mi>w</mi><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></math>, find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> expressing your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>multiplying first equation by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi></math> OR multiplying LHS and RHS of both equations<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>*</mo><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>w</mi></math></strong></em>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mi>w</mi><mo>*</mo><mi>z</mi><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>z</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</m